Sampled from west side because there were two bull snakes.

Vulink not uploading data. Visit connect to sonde was at 1059. Added twist tie to sonde housing lock. Vulink wouldn’t even turn on and stay lit up, so I took batteries (fancy purple ones) out and waited. Didn’t work, so put new batteries in (black non rechargeable). Took a minute, but eventually connected to VuSitu. Downloaded log and started a new one. The sonde may have left the water a few times while the log was running (test upload showed negative depth at first, but then next 15 min it said 1.5ft). In order to check depth, had to disconnect and reconnect to sonde so there is a small blip of logging, likely. Greased sonde housing up. Hit sonde housing with lock because couldn’t get it open for a minute.
Removed housing debris by chucking it across the river. None seemed to be impacting the sonde, but it looked like it might become problematic.

Flows very high, needed boots to get to sonde. Conductivity fluctuated from unstabilized to nominal so restored calib defaults on conductivity (and chl-a because readings were pretty high (reading in the 2 range)). That didn’t work for conductivity, so took sensor out and dried off the inside. That worked. Water had a higher amount of sediment than usual. Changed batteries.

Changed batteries. FDOM stabilized on at 15.4, measurement out of range. Conductivity measurement out of range as well. Restored calibration default for conductivity, didn’t work. Dried off inside of sensor instead, that worked. High flows, rock stuck inside restrictor. Noticeable sediment on sonde.

Conductivity not calibrated because ran out of fluid, everything else calibrated with minimal DI because DI was running low. High flows. Barriers replaced on vu and troll, but the aqua troll reading 57% even after replacing with new batteries. No Kim wipes for filter tower.
No conductivity calib because ran out of solution. Rinsed with little DI because running out of that. Batteries changed. High flows. No Kim wipes for filter tower.
High flows
Cloudy skies and warm. Pretty high flows today, medium turbidity. Will filter in lab
Batteries replaced, couldn’t get above 53% even with putting in one time use batteries. Flows high, water super clear. Easy calibration.

Sensor faces were extremely dirty. Changed batteries on troll, alkaline batteries read in 90s, but rechargeable batteries are being read in the 50s. Dropped chl-a filter on dirt ground (picked up w tweezers), but nothing got on it. Some connection issues with the adaptor thing. FDOM out of range at 11.997, restored calib defaults and dried off (neither action was necessary, but precautionary).

An aquatic plant was stuck inside the restrictor, so turbidity was like 400 (should be like 10-20). Calibrations went well. Chla filter was ripping easily during folding, but not during filtering it seemed.
Duplicate taken. Very hot day, 92°+, clear skies, low-medium turbidity. Will filter in lab.
Duplicate taken. Very hot day, 92°+, clear skies, low-medium turbidity. Will filter in lab.

Rechargeable batteries only got to 71%. Conductivity fluctuated between nominal and unstabilized. Dried off sensor. Restored calib default for conductivity, that worked after small fluctuation. Dirty sensor with worms everywhere including sensor faces. Come with brush next time because sonde was so gross.

Some reconnected at one point and a log started, so perhaps a bad data point?
Just cleaning because turb had the upwards trend. No worms, removed caps. Sonde faces were gross, had the weird pollen looking sediment streaks on faces. Everything went back to normal after.
No snakes
Very bubbly water...DO was super low on the probe. Barely filtered 500, was going really slowly.

Interior was not very dirty. Samples taken, filtered in field. Site is not very accessible anymore as vegetation is very tall and dense, came across 2 snakes in the veg.

Sensor housing and sonde were pretty clean despite a high turbidity. Cleaned and calibrated sondes, no apparent issues with either. We are leaving the caps off both CSU and CU sondes. Clear skies and warm/hot, high turbidity. Samples gathered, filtered in field.

Sonde died before we arrived. Put in new alkaline batteries and turned on just fine. Sampled, cond sensor seemed to agree more with sensor. Calibrated sonde, everything was quite easy and redeployed. Chla was still high on sensor .07 which is surprising. Turb dropped a bit to 5 ntu. Redeployment went well.

Conductivity didn’t work at first, but did after just restarting. Flows are low. Aquatroll update.

No Turb or DO calibration, redo conductivity because it was reading high numbers. Filtered in field. Flows quite low and turbidity quite low as well. Vu batteries replaced now at 100%

Tried to clear out as much sediment and algae around the sonde that I could, the sediment flowed away black, almost oily. We left the restrictor cap off

All parameters reading in new log as of first interval. Did not probe today as probe is poorly calibrated and in NESB. Filtered in field.

Clear skies at time of sampling, hot. Alexander fire smoke has made a dramatic shift in direction since sampling at Boxelder ~20 minutes ago. Smoke Now headed due north by northeast, directly toward spring creek. Sonde updated and cleaned. Sonde was extremely yuck with sludge buildup on exterior and interior. Turbidity was reading values 100+. Reading fine now.

Clear skies a of now, hot. Alexander fire smoke is nearing the site and is headed due north. Water is crystal clear, the sonde was reading turb values over 700, however, the sensor was clear of debris or grime. Cleaned and now reading appropriate values around 3. The sonde did not need to be updated unlike the other sites. Will filter in lab.

Temp on probe RDO was reading air temp (18.2), but the cond was reading the water (7.8) so used cond temp. Turb reading 4, but water looks very clear/likely less than 4. Started pouring chlorophyll bottle before a filter was on filter tower. Because of this lost a lot of sample. Salvaged what I could buy pouring what was in the top of the tower back into the bottle.

Turb was a lower than JOEI, .99 here, but looked about the same. Used cond temp again on probe, other one was reading air (tried dunking more of the RDO probe in water to see if that made a difference. It did not).
Same flows as last time, used probe temp from cond.

Used temp from cond part of probe, DO was lower and cond was higher than the log. Probed in a slower area of water and upstream than sonde, but Andrew tried double checking and probe read similar values right near sonde. Depth is at 1 ft and you can see the sonde from the rocks.

Clear skies and hot, low turbidity. Flows are low as well. Alexander fire is in effect, however, the smoke is undetectable from PBR, although the sky is hazy. Did the same thing as JOEI chla, poured sample without filter so lost some sample.

Downloaded logs, troll log ended on 9/1 likely due to power draw issue, it was ready 0 %battery even though the batteries seemed to be replaced recently and were alkaline. When I replaced them, it still thought it was 0%. Factory reset and then let it sit for a while with no batteries, connected with my phone and it started back up with 100%. When I tried to restart the logs, it thought depth was 25 ft (rather than .88). Started a log on the vulink , which corrected the pressure reading and then corrected saw depth as .88. Sensor had some gunk but it cleaned up nice and values did not adjust significantly. Turb is maybe a bit low ? Sunny, much lower flows than last Friday. Filtered in field.

Flows lower than previous sampling. Water relatively clear but still lots of benthic algae. Filtered in lab
Final sampling for the season. Channel not completely frozen but lots of snow/ice on the banks. Filtered in field

Hold on for season. Ice getting high on banks, made a difficult sound out. Stage measurement not accurate due to ice fall values on sun looks good, although temperature was negative likely due to ice formation. Chlorophyll was relatively high for the stream this time of year, may be interference due to ice forming on rocks affecting sensor.Stored cable in plastic bag with cap and two layers of electrical tape. Filtered in the field.
Pulled sonde for season and sampled for last time. Sunny day. Log  values looked great before pulling the sonde and sonde itself was not too dirty. Filtered sample and blank in field.
Pulled sonde for season and sampled for last time. Sunny day. Log  values looked great before pulling the sonde and sonde itself was not too dirty. Filtered sample and blank in field.
Warm and sunny day. Sonde in low flow housing. Filtered in lab
Strong green tint to water and medium turbidity. Sunny and warm. Medium flows. Filtered in lab
Sampled at discharge gage. Flows lower than normal and turbidity about normal. Lots of benthic algae in stream and detaching. Filtered in lab
Lots of algae at site and on housing. Water level very low and slow. Sampled with swing sampler and filtered in lab
Flows very low and slow. Lots of large algae floating on the surface. Warm and sunny. Filtered in lab
Water relatively clear with decent flow. Slight greenness to water but lower then usually. Filtered in lab
Sunny but forecasted storm later. Flows higher and has slight tint to it. Little suspended sediment. Filtered in lab
Flows higher and more turbid. Sunny with storm forecasted. Filtered in lab
Flows higher but water not very turbid. Cloudy weather. Filtered in lab. Stage plate at 39 cm
Water a bit more turbid with slight brown color. Little large suspended sediment. Sunny. Filtered in lab
Flows about the same as last site visit and water less turbid but has brown color to it. Sunny. Filtered in lab.
Flows about the same as last site visit and water less turbid but has brown color to it. Sunny. Filtered in lab.

Reservoir releasing some flow but little to no active benthic algae. Filtered in lab
Post snow. Filtered in lab
Flows much higher and a bit more turbid but not much large suspended sediment. Rain yesterday and areas today. Filtered in lab
Flows about the same (pleasent valley canal running) not too turbid. Cloudy. Filtered in lan
Post rain, flows higher and much more turbid. Sunny. Filtered in lab
Flows higher and water more turbid but slightly less than pbd. Post rain. Filtered in lab
Flows up and Turbidity about the same. Hotshot crew in parking lot for some reason. Checked sonde values but did not clean yet. Filtered in lab
Flows about the same. Sunny. Lot very turbid. Filtered in field
Sunny. Sampled at site as snow has melted some.  Lower flows and not much algae or turbidity. Filtered in the field.
Clear skies, warm, medium-low turbidity. Will filter in lab
Flows still lower and water quite clear. Storm rolling in? Filtered in field. Checked sonde values before sampling.
Clear skies, warm, low turbidity. Lots of algal growth. Filtered in lab
Clear skies, warm, low turbidity, immense algal buildup. Cleared housing of algae. Will filter in lab.

Clear skies, warm, high turbidity. 
Will filter in lab.

Some rain but sampled before effects. Flows higher but turbidity about the same. New stage plate installed( measurement taken on it). Filtered in lab
Flows are kind of low, so probe wasn’t vertical. It was more sideways.
Low flows, pretty clear water

Sonde was completely caked in sediment and had high chla, high turbidity and low FDOM.  Cleaned up nicely.  Swapped sensors and calibrated FDOM. SC dropped slightly. pH was reading low, topped off the junction fluid and values went up a bit, may just take a while to stabilize. Started logs and test uploaded. Flows are much higher with lots of suspended sediment.
Flows way up. Turbidity about the same but more large sediment. Filtered In field.

Flows much higher, turbidity a bit higher but not by much. Sonde was not very dirty but still removed cap for the next month. Values agreed well post Cal other than pH but perhaps it just needs time to adjust? Filtered in field
High flows, turbidity about the same, water has amber tint. Filtered in field
Cloudy, slightly snowy, medium turbidity, cold. Will filter in lab.
Cloudy, cool, windy, medium turbidity. Filtered in lab
Cloudy, little bit of snow, cool, medium-low turbidity. Will filter in lab.
Cloudy, little bit of snow, cool, medium-low turb. Will filter in lab
Visited site for water sampling. Clear, sunny conditions with some wind. Low flow at site, water clarity is high. Filtered chlorophyll-a in the lab.
Sunny, windy. Flows much higher and Turbidity about normal for site. Removed debris from sensor housing. Filtered for chla in lab
Sunny, flows a bit higher than yesterday. Water a bit turbid with small particulates. Filtered for chla in lab
Sunny, flows a bit higher than yesterday. Water a bit turbid with small particulates. Filtered for chla in lab
Water sampling site visit. Clear, sunny day with some wind. High algae content in water, low turbidity and high clarity. Filtered for chlorophyll-a in the lab.
Sunny, higher flows than yesterday and decent turbidity. Filtered Chla in lab
Water sampling visit. Mostly sunny and clear, few clouds and breezy. Pretty clear water, lower flow. Filtered chlorophyll-a in the lab.

Deployed donde at site for the season. Snow was melted around housing and were able to deploy easily. Need to replace the carabiner in the housing cap. All values looked normal for the site. Flows lower than I would expect but there was a storm yesterday so melt may have been delayed. Water very clear and no benthic algae at the site. Filtered in the field.
Site sampling, sunny, cool and breezy. Water has high clarity, lower flow than normal. No algae present. Filtered in field
Sunny, higher flows with a bit more benthic algae. Not too turbid but slight green tint to cloudiness. Filtered in field.
Water sampling site visit. Partly cloudy, warm. Regular flow, pretty clear water.

Site visit to collect water samples and check the pH sensor. Clear, sunny day with few clouds, slight wind. Water level is normal with high clarity. One of the lower securing metal bands was broken so we secured it. The housing was moving/bouncing slightly due to this. Plan to bring a new sensor to change next week.
Before storm. Decent amount of benthic algae growing on rock and sonde housing. Low turbidity and normal flows. Filtered in lab
Flows have come down significantly since last week and water is much clearer. Before rain. Filtered in lab
Flows lower and very clear. Sunny. Filtered in lab
Overcast, cool, misty morning, Rainfall last night. Higher flows than last week and lower water clarity. Filtered chlorophyll-a in the lab.
Overcast, cool, cloudy and misty conditions. Higher flows than last week with lower clarity. Filtered chlorophyll-a in the lab.
Mostly cloudy and cool, rainfall last night. Sampled water below bridge. High flow and still fairly clear water. Filtered chlorophyll in the lab.
Cloudy, active rainfall during sampling, cool temperature. Higher flows than last week with lower clarity. Filtered chlorophyll in the lab.
Flows way higher. Water not much more turbid. In between light rain and sun. Filtered in lab
Flows way higher. Water not much more turbid. In between light rain and sun. Filtered in lab
Flows higher due to release. Water still quite clear and not too much benthic algae growing. Filtered in lab
Flows much higher and more turbid. Sunny. Filtered in lab
Cloudy weather with rain likely. Flows much higher and less snow at site. Filtered in lab.
Higher flows, sunny. Filtered in lab. TOC/Chla/turb only!!
Sunny. High flows, high ish turb. Filtered in lab
Sunny, higher flows, low turb. Some suspended leaf litter. Filtered in lab
Sunny, high flows. Decent amount of suspended sediment. Filtered in lab
Flows much higher with suspended material being recirculated. Filtered in lab
Mostly cloudy, spotty sun and cool. Possible rain overnight. High water flow, colder water temperature, and still high clarity. Filtered chlorA in the lab.
Partly cloudy, increasing sun. Possible rain overnight, and cool. High water flows, ~72cfs and high water clarity. Filtered chlorA in the lab. PVC housing looks good and unobstructed.

Partly cloudy and cool, overnight rain. High flows out of reservoir but water has high clarity and typical EC and RDO. Filtered chlorA in the lab. The pvc sensor housing is clear and free. 

Slight mishap in the lab with the filter tower and wasn’t able to capture 1000 mL.
Mostly cloudy, cool, and breezy. Overnight rain likely. Water is flowing pretty high, lower EC than upper sites, high water clarity. PVC sensor housing is clear. Filtered chlorA in the lab.

Mostly sunny, a little breeze. Rain overnight and heavy short rain 10 minutes before sampling. High flows, high clarity, and lower EC than upper sites. Removed a few branches/sticks from sensor housing. Housing is still attached strongly to rocks and anchors. Filtered chlorA in the lab.
Mostly sunny with a few clouds and breezy. High water flow, ~72cfs, with pretty high clarity. The pvc sonde housing is sound and unobstructed. Filtered chlorA in the lab.
Mostly cloudy, breezy, cool. High river flow and water is mostly clear. Filtered chlorA in the lab.
Overcast, rain clouds moving through, cool and breezy. High flows, EC is lower than JOEI, without sunlight, clarity is low. Filtered chlorA in the lab.
High flows but not too turbid. Filtered in lab. Sunny

Water sampling visit. Partly cloudy and warm, mosquito season has arrived. River is flowing high and quickly with low clarity, sediment visible in the water. Filtered chlorA in the lab. Snake skin/skeleton by the sampling spot, be aware.

Warm and sunny morning,  few clouds, cooler at the river and buggy. Water level is high, quick flows, and pretty brown. Clarity is lower than last week and you can see sediment in the water. Took a duplicate at this location today. Filtered chlorA in the lab.

Warm and sunny morning,  few clouds, cooler at the river and buggy. Water level is high, quick flows, and pretty brown. Clarity is lower than last week and you can see sediment in the water. Took a duplicate at this location today. Filtered chlorA in the lab.
Sunny and warm for water sampling. Slight breeze, high flows at ~80-82 cfs. Water is still pretty clear. Filtered chlorA onsite.

Sunny and warm with slight breeze for water sampling visit. Water is moving quickly, higher level than last week though still pretty clear. Filtered sample at site. The pvc housing may have become disconnected at the lower anchor like we saw a couple weeks ago. It was moving and flexing with the river. I didn’t have tools or waders to fix and discover more.

Sunny, increasing clouds, slightly breezy, warm. High flows and slightly brown tinged water. Mostly clear, but sunlight glare and high flows so hard to see through the water. Filtered chlorA on site. The transmitter cable was exposed at one short section on the bridge near the transmitter. Taped for now.
Partly cloudy, rain forming, warm and buggy. Water level js high, somewhat brown but still quite clear. Filtered chlorA onsite.
Overcast, cooler with clouds, started to sprinkle last few minutes I was there. Water is flowing high, ~82-85 cds but still good clarity. Higher EC than lower downstream. Filtered chlorA onsite.
Rain clouds moved in, cooler, a little breezy. Water level is high with high clarity, EC is just below 40. Filtered chlorA onsite.
Sampled while on site for cleaning. Filtered in lab. Flows decently high and a bit turbid.
Sampled upstream of bridge due to upwelling DS of the bridge. Filtered in lab. Sunny and lots of suspended sediment.
Not too turbid. Pre light rain. Filtered in field.

Sunny and warm day, little to no breeze. Updated the software for the vulink and AQ. Took water samples just below the sonde housing in the river. Cleaned sonde sensors and turbidity seemed to go back to a reasonable level. Lots of spiders in the housing, the sonde itself was dirty, but cleaned easily. Battery levels are getting low but I think should last for 2 weeks. Downloaded logs and started new ones. Test upload successful.

Sunny and warm day with little breeze. Updated vulink and troll. Toon chlorA and total OC water samples while updating. Cleaned sonde when updates complete. Ants were in the housing lid, and the sonde was quite dirty. Easily cleaned with water. Cleaning improved the readings. Redeployed, downloaded logs, and started new ones. Test upload successful.
Clear skies, sunny, and cool without breeze. Heavy rain yesterday and the flow is high, with low clarity. Sampled water, will update sonde next week with calibrations.

Clear skies, sun hadn’t gotten over the canyon walls yet, and cool. Heavy rain event yesterday and flows are high still but river is quite clear here. Sampling was quick. Filtered chlorA in the field.
Sunny, clear day with little breeze. Heavy rain yesterday and flows are still high, ~78cfs. Water clarity is high too. Filtered chlorA on site.
Sunny, rain yesterday. Water about the same level as Friday and not very turbid. Filtered at CHD later on.
Sunny, lower flows than last week but still very high. Not much Turbidity. Filtered on site.
Sunny and clear with little breeze. High flows still from reservoir, water is pretty clear though. Sampled water and filter chlorA on site.
Sunny, clear, breezy and warm day at JOEI. Sampled water and filtered chlorA in the field.
Flows high but generally decreasing. Water not very turbid. Filtered in lab

Overcast but warm, no breeze. River flows are still good and the clarity is high, low turbidity. Downloaded logs, swapped sensores and calibrated FDOM. Redeployed, restarted logs. Sampled water, filtered in the lab, and grabbed the camera.

Overcast and warm, n o breeze. Updated vulink and troll. Troll said failed, but when I checked, all firmware was up to date. Went ahead with calibrations and cleaning. Changed troll batteries, still reading low. Downloaded logs, started new ones. Took water samples. Filtered chlorA in the lab. Test upload success.

Overcast, a little breeze and warm. Collected water samples, filtered in the lab. Cleaned sensors, swapped batteries in vulink. Changed old sensors for calibrated ones. Did FDOM calibration, redeployed sonde. Started new logs. Test upload failed due to antenna breaking.
Flows a bit higher and cond lower than usual. Still somewhat turbid. Sunny. Filtered in lab
Sampled upstream of the bridge due to side channel. Sunny, water quite clear. Filtered in lab
Cloudy but lots of benthic algae at site. Filtered in lab.
Lower flows than previous sample. Water quite clear and fast moving (not much suspended sediment). Before rain event. Filtered in lab
Sunny and cool with a slight breeze. Fish hanging out in the stream, high clarity and flows are coming down. Filtered in the lab.

Sunny, slight breeze, cool. Water flows are lower, around 66cfs and water is quite clear. Sampled water, filtered for chlorA in the lab. Switched sensors this week, downloaded log and started a new one. The batteries are getting low, ~28%, replace next week perhaps. The sonde kept saying the troll was open, but all readings were fine and I redeployed with calibrated sensors. Data looks good and started a new log.
Sunny and clear. Water is clear and moving swiftly. Filtered chlorA in the lab.
Sunny and clear. Water is clear and moving swiftly. Filtered chlorA in the lab.
Sunny, mostly clear day, few clouds and slight breeze. Road work at pfal bridge continues. Flow is good but decreasing, high clarity and low EC. Filtered chlorA in the lab.
Sunny, warm and clear day. River is flowing well, low EC, low turbidity, high clarity. The sonde housings are barely attached and need some major work. Filtered chlorA in the lab.
Partly cloudy and warm, a little breeze. River is around 66cfs high clarity, and low EC. sampled water and filtered chlorA in the lab.
Mostly sunny, warm, a few clouds and wind. River seems lower here, but clarity is still pretty high and turbidity seems a little higher too. Collected samples, filtered chlorA in the lab.
Sunny and warm day. River is typical here and more turbid with visible sediment. However still pretty clear. Sampled water and filtered chlorA in the lab.
Lower flows, sunny, very clear water and filtered in the lab.
Took water samples and filtered chlorA onsite. Sunny, warm, and typical flows with a little green tinge to the water but still quite clear. SC and DO are normal.
Sampled water and filtered chlorA onsite. Water is clear and still flowing well but is decreasing. Sunny, warm and a little breezy.
Flows much lower and water still quite clear. Sunny. Filtered in field
Sunny, high flows, not much Turbidity. Filtered in field
Sampled water and filtered chlorA in the field. Clouds are moving in, no breeze. Flows are decreasing and are at ~55cfs, high clarity.
Sunny, flowsuvh lower and water very clear. Greyling fish present in high numbers. Filtered in field.
Flows lower. Clear water with some floating leaf litter from wind, little suspended sediment.
Sunny, breezy, and warm day for water sampling. The water is really clear, decent flow still. Filtered chlorA at SFM.
Sunny, breezy, and warm day for water sampling. The water is really clear, decent flow still. Filtered chlorA at SFM.
Sunny and warm with a little breeze. High water clarity and decent flow. Sampled water and filtered chlorA at SFM.

Water sampling and sensor cleaning visit. Connection folks were not present. Partly cloudy day, sprinkled at times, windy. Sampled water, no issues. Cleaned the sonde, downloaded the log, redeployed and started the log. Optical readings did improve. The troll was showing low battery, so I replaced with new batteries but it still shows low.  Filtered chlorA onsite.
Cloudy and warm day. Sampled water and filtered chlorA onsite. Flows are still high, water is clear.
Partly cloudy, warm, slight breeze. Sampled water, sonde looks good. Flows pretty high right now, good clarity. Filtered chlorA in the field and there was a lot of organic matter.
Sunny, some clouds and slight breeze. Water is at a normal level and quite clear. Sampled water and filtered ChlorA at JoeI.
Mostly sunny up at this location, some breeze. Warm, low flows and very clear water. Sampled water, filtered on site.
